column4: sun-java6-bin is making me dead inside.  Has anyone actually made this install on 8.04?
yes.  Pastebin your cause of death
- I can do that!
- Seems a lot of people get the same output I do during install.
http://sadsoftware.blogspot.com/2008/07/installing-jdk-in-openvz-vps.html seems to have an explanation
- I looked at that, but I don't have OpenVZ, nor that beancounter stuff in /proc
- Some of the threads say I'll get this install error if I failed to check the box when the license for Java was displayed.  If that's the case, how on earth do you get another chance?
are you installing in a shell?
- First time, when it got screwed up, was in Symantic.  Now I'm in a shell.  I can do either.
'sudo dpkg --configure -a' doesn't give you the license question?
- Negative.  subprocess post-installation script returned error exit status 134
can you purge it?
- Been tere, done that.  Will do ita agian
oh, you're on dapper too?
- Whatever 8.04 is called.  Too many bird to remember.
ah, yeah, the package version confused me
- Purged.  Recommendation on how to reload it?
sudo apt-get install sun-java6-bin
- Amazing!  It's installed!  I *know* I've done that before!
- Thanks!
yeah that happens sometimes :)
- I'm gonna claim the position of the moon changed.  :-)
